overview: The user wanted a significant aesthetic upgrade for their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they described as visually unappealing. The agent
  initiated a comprehensive redesign, starting with a new sleep-themed color
  palette and custom CSS utilities. This led to a complete overhaul of the main
  form layout, including a new progress indicator and card styling. The
  introduction section was transformed with a hero element and interactive
  feature cards. All core UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders,
  and progress bars were restyled for a polished look. Crucially, all 14
  questionnaire sections were updated to align with the new theme, replacing
  generic gray boxes with visually appealing card-style groupings and enhanced
  form field interactions. During the process, a console error related to null
  input values was identified and fixed by modifying the  component to
  safely handle such values. The result is a much more cohesive, calming, and
  professional-looking application, moving away from a generic template feel to
  a tailored sleep health experience.
